Case-management and case-analysis skills will be taught: planning and conducting assessment interviews and testing, data gathering and analysing, conceptualization and presentation of case material. In practicums participants' work with patients is supervised and skills are rehearsed. Main prerequisite to admission to the course is practice in clinical psychology.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Introduction to the basic skills of case analysis in clinical psychology.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Acquisition of evidence-based approach to methods of psychological assessment and intervention.  Knowledge of basic approaches to case conceptualization and evaluation. Skills of case management, assessment and intervention planning, interpretation of results and report writing.
